1. Purpose
This Technology Control Plan establishes the procedures and controls required to protect export-controlled technology, technical data, software, and Controlled Unclassified Information (CUI) at AnySignal.
It ensures compliance with the Export Administration Regulations (EAR), International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) where applicable, and DFARS/NIST 800-171 requirements for CUI while enabling rapid engineering velocity in RF, DSP, and satellite communications development.
2. Scope
This TCP applies to all Securitl personnel, contractors, visitors, and systems handling:
AnyLink platform and adaptive waveform libraries
DSP software and interference-mitigation algorithms
RF/signal processing systems (waveforms, spectrum analysis)
Satellite communications technical data and firmware
Any CUI received under DoD or federal contracts
Model weights, telemetry, and operational datasets (if classified as controlled)
3. Controlled Technology & Classification
All items are initially classified as EAR dual-use (primarily CCL Categories 3, 5, and 9).
No confirmed ITAR-controlled items at this time (USML review completed).
Future defense programs will trigger re-classification and potential ITAR controls.
CUI marking and protection required for any federal contract data.
4. System Boundary Model (Three-Zone Architecture)

Controlled Zone (Restricted / High-Sensitivity)
AI/DSP model weights, waveform libraries, CUI datasets, restricted repos, RF/signal processing systems, firmware/embedded software. Controls: US-person access where required • FIPS 140-3 validated cryptographic modules • Full audit logging & monitoring • No uncontrolled egress.
Boundary Layer (Enforcement & Control Point)
IAM/Authentication, RBAC & Policies, Approval Workflows, Logging & SIEM, Secure Data Transfer. Controls: Just-in-time / auditable access • All crossings logged • No uncontrolled bypass.
General Engineering Zone (Day-to-Day Work)
Dev/Test environments, internal collaboration tools, CI/CD pipelines, non-sensitive workflows. Controls: Enterprise IAM/MFA • No controlled data storage unless explicitly approved • Sanitized outputs only.
5. Physical Security Controls
Controlled Zone areas will be segregated (badged access, locked cabinets, visitor logs).
Floorplans of Torrance and LA facilities attached as Appendix A (updated as needed).
Controlled equipment labeled “Export Controlled / Restricted Use”.
6. Information Technology & Data Controls
Controlled data stored only in approved enclaves (e.g., AWS GovCloud or equivalent with FIPS encryption).
No controlled data on personal devices or public clouds unless approved and encrypted.
All transfers between zones require documented approval workflows and logging.
HSM/PKI stack used for key management (multi-tenancy for commercial vs. federal partitions).
7. Personnel & Access Controls
Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) enforced.
Foreign persons/visitors: screened and restricted from Controlled Zone unless licensed.
Annual access reviews and training required for all personnel.
8. Training & Awareness
All employees receive initial and annual export compliance training.
Specific TCP training for anyone accessing Controlled Zone.
9. Auditing, Monitoring & Incident Response
Quarterly TCP assessments and internal audits.
Immediate reporting of any suspected violation to the Export Compliance Officer.
Incident response plan includes containment, investigation, and voluntary disclosure if required.
10. Export Licensing & Deemed Exports
Deemed export reviews required before foreign-person access to technical data.
License applications prepared and submitted as needed (BIS for EAR, DDTC for ITAR).
End-user/end-use screening mandatory for all shipments and collaborations.
11. Recordkeeping
All TCP-related records retained for minimum 5 years.
Electronic storage in approved secure repository.
12. Review, Modification & Termination
Annual recertification by Export Compliance Officer.
Immediate update required for any changes (new tech, personnel, contracts, facility moves).
Upon termination: controlled items/data disposition coordinated with Export Compliance Officer.
